      "writtenOn": "2026-02-05T15:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking back at this change 5 years later, my objection persists.\n\n\u003e Eeven if the replication has successfully completed, the change will still be in the index: removing it from the index is precisely the intent of this subscriber\u0027s handler, so we should be sure the change is still sitting in the index .\n\nThat\u0027s not true, at least for the master branch of multi-site.\n\nThe multi-site plugin listens for pull-replication events and, for ref updates associated with a /meta ref-update, processes them and causes the removal of the change from the index.\n\nIMHO, we should:\n\na. Avoid making one call to the index, using also a deprecated lookup by id, which would just cause additional unneeded load.\nb. Just return `true` and leave the work of updating the index to the appropriate processor of the indexing events.",
      "parentUuid": "34f6cf1c_cf24ad23",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 64,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 64,
        "endChar": 93
